      "text": "I’ve planned the keyframes across the six-shot sequence.\n\nCurrent shape:\n- SHOT-01: 1 start keyframe\n- SHOT-02: 1 start keyframe\n- SHOT-03: 1 start keyframe\n- SHOT-04: 2 keyframes — start and end, because this shot has a meaningful change from rushing arrival to dismount-and-bolt\n- SHOT-05: 1 start keyframe\n- SHOT-06: 1 start keyframe\n\nSo the sequence uses 7 keyframes total.\n\nCreatively, that’s the right balance:\n- the chase beats mostly need one strong anchor each\n- the arrival shot is the only one that really benefits from a second frame\n- the library reveal and donkey button work better with clean, controlled single anchors rather than overcomplicating them\n\nNext I’d move straight into preparing the keyframe prompts so the stills are ready to generate."
